<p>Under this model, the posterior predictive distribution for a new observation [latex]\tilde{y}[/latex], [latex]p(\tilde{y} \mid y_1, \ldots, y_n)[/latex] is the optimal density estimator (under squared error loss).  Samples for this estimator can be easily computed from the samples generated by our MCMC:</p>

